CPT MISSION STATEMENT
Provide education and training that is sustainable through a continuous programme of reinforcing conformance in both work and product quality, based on quality assurance principles and mechanisms.


Read more

 
 










Production & Manufacturing
These qualifications specify the key skills, knowledge and values required to access occupationally focused qualifications in the manufacturing, & related sectors in the FET Band.

 




Supply Chain & Logistics
These qualifications reflect some of the needs of the Wholesale and Retail sector both now and in the future as it developed following much discussion with Wholesalers, Distribution Centres and Mail Order Houses.

 




Special Industries
CPT is able to contextualise programmes to include the unique processes & policies of any of its clients ensuring that learners receive both academic and industry-specific knowledge.

 




Supervision
A person acquiring these qualifications will be able to lead a team of people, schedule resources; monitor quality control practices within a specialized manufacturing or other engineering related industries.

 

 




SKILLS DEVELOPMENT SOLUTIONS The CPT education and training vision is based on short and long-range effects in the workplace. It has a vision of establishing a workplace model of worker self-management, empowerment and growing productivity in which education and training is outcomes-based and learning is a lifelong process rather than a once-off experience.
  









